1
00:00:22,655 --> 00:00:24,289
I'm so sorry.

2
00:00:24,290 --> 00:00:25,824
Thank you.

3
00:00:25,825 --> 00:00:26,893
Good morning.

4
00:00:30,563 --> 00:00:31,630
Good morning, Ran.

5
00:00:31,631 --> 00:00:32,831
Good morning.

6
00:00:32,832 --> 00:00:35,168
You see,
I'm already having a hectic morning.

7
00:00:35,769 --> 00:00:37,102
I'm leaving it here.

8
00:00:37,103 --> 00:00:38,003
Thank you.

9
00:00:38,004 --> 00:00:39,638
This is too troublesome.

10
00:00:39,639 --> 00:00:42,074
Garbage rules in Japan are so annoying.

11
00:00:42,075 --> 00:00:44,309
Each country has its own rules.

12
00:00:44,310 --> 00:00:47,312
As they say, when in Rome,
do as the Romans do.

13
00:00:47,313 --> 00:00:48,347
<i>Ni hao.</i>

14
00:00:48,348 --> 00:00:51,551
Good morning. Wait a minute. Hold on.

15
00:00:52,285 --> 00:00:53,820
Hand me that bag.

16
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,122
- The bag? Okay.
- Yes. Hurry up.

17
00:00:56,656 --> 00:00:59,292
‎Here it is.

18
00:01:01,494 --> 00:01:03,128
Eat this for lunch.

19
00:01:03,129 --> 00:01:04,263
I'm sure you'll love it.

20
00:01:04,264 --> 00:01:06,433
Really? I'm so happy.

21
00:01:07,434 --> 00:01:09,402
<i>Xie xie,</i> Auntie Ma.

22
00:01:11,471 --> 00:01:12,405
Come on now.

23
00:01:12,972 --> 00:01:15,708
Could you please
at least tell me your name?

24
00:01:25,952 --> 00:01:29,422
You didn't pay your taxi fare
and had illegal drugs.

25
00:01:30,657 --> 00:01:34,893
Where did you get
all that liquid marijuana

26
00:01:34,894 --> 00:01:36,396
you had in your bag?

27
00:01:51,077 --> 00:01:54,414
- What did she say?
- "That bag is not mine."

28
00:01:56,182 --> 00:01:59,586
Are you talking about the small bag
with liquid marijuana in it?

29
00:02:00,286 --> 00:02:03,123
Then, why would your urine test
come back positive?

30
00:02:05,291 --> 00:02:07,427
Maybe you were planning to sell them off.

31
00:02:17,003 --> 00:02:18,003
I'm so sorry.

32
00:02:18,004 --> 00:02:19,304
Have a great time at school.

33
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:21,406
We will.

34
00:02:21,407 --> 00:02:22,941
‎INTERNATIONAL INVESTIGATION DIVISION
‎HIGASHI SHINJUKU POLICE STATION

35
00:02:22,942 --> 00:02:26,178
Why wouldn't she confess
when there's evidence?

36
00:02:26,179 --> 00:02:29,348
I bet she's underestimating
the Japanese police force.

37
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:31,084
Come on now. Let's go back.

38
00:02:33,686 --> 00:02:36,122
Yeah, yeah. Oh really?

39
00:02:36,923 --> 00:02:39,993
Stop repeating "do that"!
Shut up and don't mess with us.

40
00:02:41,928 --> 00:02:44,596
You had to come in so early
in the morning.

41
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:48,400
Having to interpret every word
those scumbags say

42
00:02:48,401 --> 00:02:50,069
must be stressful for you.

43
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:54,174
I'm fine
because I don't involve my emotions.

44
00:02:55,875 --> 00:02:57,509
- Hey, Shakuno.
- Yes, sir?

45
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:58,577
Where the heck is Koda?

46
00:02:58,578 --> 00:03:00,513
How should I know?

47
00:03:01,214 --> 00:03:04,716
We've got
so many questioning sessions lined up.

48
00:03:04,717 --> 00:03:06,419
Where's the Lettuce Head?

49
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:09,689
Lettuce Head?

50
00:03:16,930 --> 00:03:18,864
- Please stop right here.
- Okay.

51
00:03:18,865 --> 00:03:22,235
Come over here. Come this way.
It's all right.

52
00:03:23,870 --> 00:03:26,506
- Okay, okay. It's all right.
- Calm down, please sir.

53
00:03:27,173 --> 00:03:29,141
I didn’t do anything.

54
00:03:29,142 --> 00:03:31,243
Residence Card.

55
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:32,911
Come on, show it to us. Don't you have it?

56
00:03:32,912 --> 00:03:35,214
- Your card.
- Really, I did nothing. No idea.

57
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:36,883
Can I look inside your bag?

58
00:03:38,818 --> 00:03:40,819
What is this?

59
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:42,956
I... I didn’t do anything.

60
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:45,658
You don't have it, do you?

61
00:03:46,192 --> 00:03:48,827
- I'm sorry.
- Come with us.

62
00:03:48,828 --> 00:03:51,630
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

63
00:03:51,631 --> 00:03:53,498
- Where are you from?
- I don’t understand.

64
00:03:53,499 --> 00:03:54,600
Vietnam.

65
00:03:54,601 --> 00:03:55,934
Are you Vietnamese?

66
00:03:55,935 --> 00:03:58,070
Do you understand Japanese?

67
00:03:58,071 --> 00:03:59,239
Sorry.

68
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:33,206
- It wasn't me. What's your problem?
- That's enough.

69
00:04:36,309 --> 00:04:37,276
Hello?

70
00:04:37,277 --> 00:04:41,480
<i>Arikino, there was a brawl
among foreigners in the Shinjuku area.</i>

71
00:04:41,481 --> 00:04:42,948
<i>Can you head over there this evening?</i>

72
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:44,284
Yes, ma'am.

73
00:05:11,711 --> 00:05:13,946
Whoa, this is a serious scorpion.

74
00:05:14,847 --> 00:05:16,382
Here I go.

75
00:05:32,865 --> 00:05:35,301
Hello? Hello?

76
00:05:37,136 --> 00:05:40,506
Where are you? I'm worried about you.
Call me.

77
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:53,953
What should I do?

78
00:06:00,059 --> 00:06:03,596
Friend... Friend... Friend...

79
00:06:06,699 --> 00:06:09,435
All right then. I'm calling for help.

80
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:15,208
What the...

81
00:06:16,776 --> 00:06:17,910
I don't have my phone.

82
00:06:18,578 --> 00:06:20,246
Where is it?

83
00:06:25,017 --> 00:06:26,252
Excuse me, sir.

84
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,922
Can I use your cellphone for a moment?

85
00:06:30,690 --> 00:06:32,190
Actually, I'm using it for work--

86
00:06:32,191 --> 00:06:34,726
Just for a moment.
Can you hold on to this?

87
00:06:34,727 --> 00:06:35,828
Miss!

88
00:06:38,631 --> 00:06:40,065
I didn't say you could use it.

89
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:42,501
Oh? Are you from China?

90
00:06:42,502 --> 00:06:43,602
No, I'm not.

91
00:06:43,603 --> 00:06:45,304
Then how do you explain this?

92
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,241
That's for my work.

93
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:50,910
Why don't you take her
to the police station?

94
00:06:52,512 --> 00:06:53,845
You heard our conversation?

95
00:06:53,846 --> 00:06:55,347
I see.

96
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:59,050
This must be fate.
Could you please help me?

97
00:06:59,051 --> 00:07:00,919
You can have it if you want.

98
00:07:00,920 --> 00:07:02,254
No, thanks.

99
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,556
Go ahead, help yourself.

100
00:07:15,601 --> 00:07:17,069
"My name is Shen Yinuo. I'm 24 years old."

101
00:07:17,837 --> 00:07:18,704
Shen.

102
00:07:24,277 --> 00:07:28,214
"I came to Japan because I want to go
to graduate school here."

103
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,555
"But I can't speak Japanese well, yet."

104
00:07:37,490 --> 00:07:39,224
You can speak in your native language.

105
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:41,694
This man here will interpret for you.

106
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:44,196
Um... I need to get back to work...

107
00:07:44,197 --> 00:07:45,364
Take a look at this.

108
00:07:48,534 --> 00:07:49,868
What did she say?

109
00:07:49,869 --> 00:07:51,838
"This is my friend Candy."

110
00:07:56,909 --> 00:07:58,811
"She has gone missing."

111
00:08:04,617 --> 00:08:07,186
Can you tell me more about it?

112
00:08:08,554 --> 00:08:13,159
I met Candy online about a month ago.

113
00:08:14,260 --> 00:08:17,429
At that time,
I had just come from Shanghai

114
00:08:17,430 --> 00:08:19,999
and was feeling homesick.

115
00:08:21,434 --> 00:08:25,203
She made her first visit
to Japan last week from Jilin Province.

116
00:08:25,204 --> 00:08:30,176
Tokyo is so lively and fun,
and we visited many places.

117
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:42,053
"Since I had to go to school yesterday,

118
00:08:42,054 --> 00:08:45,056
she went to buy her favorite
anime merchandise on her own.

119
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:47,493
And she hasn't come back since."

120
00:08:52,965 --> 00:08:55,101
So, there's been no reply

121
00:08:55,735 --> 00:08:58,004
for 20 hours since last evening...

122
00:09:02,909 --> 00:09:04,744
Here is my business card.

123
00:09:06,412 --> 00:09:08,314
MARI KODA
HIGASHI SHINJUKU POLICE STATION

124
00:09:14,120 --> 00:09:15,121
Are you really a detective?

125
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:19,190
Actually, many people ask me that.

126
00:09:19,191 --> 00:09:21,060
They wonder if I'm really a detective.

127
00:09:24,931 --> 00:09:25,798
Thanks.

128
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,367
Mr. Arikino.

129
00:09:29,368 --> 00:09:30,669
RYO ARIKINO
INTERPRETATION CENTER

130
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,972
Oh my goodness! You're one of us?

131
00:09:33,573 --> 00:09:37,076
I've only been with this division
for about a month now.

132
00:09:38,644 --> 00:09:40,680
Where's the Lettuce Head?

133
00:09:41,614 --> 00:09:43,249
Lettuce Head...

134
00:09:45,017 --> 00:09:48,721
Well, well, well...
How should we go about finding Candy?

135
00:09:50,756 --> 00:09:53,391
Did you just sneer
like some cartoon characters do?

136
00:09:53,392 --> 00:09:54,594
No, I didn't.

137
00:09:55,428 --> 00:09:57,395
Are you really going to look for her?

138
00:09:57,396 --> 00:09:59,098
Why do you ask?

139
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:04,170
It's not uncommon for some foreigners
to go missing in Japan.

140
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:09,541
Some come here on a tourist visa
and stay even after it expires,

141
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:12,578
while others come
with the intention of disappearing.

142
00:10:13,212 --> 00:10:16,215
Besides, you don't know
if she's being truthful.

143
00:10:17,617 --> 00:10:19,851
Isn't it too soon to say she's missing

144
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:22,121
after just a day out of contact?

145
00:10:24,557 --> 00:10:27,860
You're more like a detective
than an interpreter.

146
00:10:31,931 --> 00:10:33,432
Okay then. I have to get going.

147
00:10:35,601 --> 00:10:36,868
Thank you.

148
00:10:36,869 --> 00:10:39,572
I just can't stand by when she needs help.

149
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:55,854
These are for today's questioning.
Review them beforehand.

150
00:10:55,855 --> 00:10:57,089
Yes, sir.

151
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:04,930
Why do I have to take care
of Koda's share of the work?

152
00:11:05,598 --> 00:11:08,867
Sir, could you please
straighten her out for once?

153
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:11,103
I don't have time
to keep covering for her.

154
00:11:14,106 --> 00:11:15,306
Actually, I've been telling her.

155
00:11:15,307 --> 00:11:18,243
Again! More assault
and prostitution cases coming our way.

156
00:11:18,244 --> 00:11:22,114
Are you sure we can afford to have
a detective like her on our team?

157
00:11:22,882 --> 00:11:24,215
He's right.

158
00:11:24,216 --> 00:11:27,619
She spends all her time
going after trivial cases like crumbs.

159
00:11:27,620 --> 00:11:32,023
But the safety guide brochure
for foreign residents she recently made

160
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:34,993
has a very good reputation, you know.

161
00:11:34,994 --> 00:11:39,298
We just have to assign
the right tasks for her, I guess.

162
00:11:49,742 --> 00:11:52,911
<i>Yoo-hoo! It's Koda
from the Higashi Shinjuku Police Station.</i>

163
00:11:52,912 --> 00:11:53,979
<i>Thanks for helping earlier.</i>

164
00:11:55,381 --> 00:11:58,951
<i>Arikeeno, how about having dinner
together? My treat.</i>

165
00:12:00,119 --> 00:12:01,353
"Arikeeno"?

166
00:12:02,822 --> 00:12:06,125
<i>I reserved a table for two at six
at an amazing Chinese restaurant.</i>

167
00:12:16,936 --> 00:12:19,038
Hi, Arikeeno! Over here.

168
00:12:20,106 --> 00:12:21,307
Arikeeno...

169
00:12:23,776 --> 00:12:26,644
- Is beer okay for you?
- Sure.

170
00:12:26,645 --> 00:12:28,080
I'm having juice.

171
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:30,849
That's a great color.

172
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:32,183
Thanks.

173
00:12:32,184 --> 00:12:33,084
It gives me energy.

174
00:12:33,085 --> 00:12:34,520
That's a score!

175
00:12:47,433 --> 00:12:49,135
Well then, cheers!

176
00:12:55,574 --> 00:12:57,343
- Are you a regular here?
- Nope, second time.

177
00:12:59,612 --> 00:13:01,980
The staff here hardly speak any Japanese,

178
00:13:01,981 --> 00:13:04,315
so I'm counting on your help.
Okay, Arikeeno?

179
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:05,817
Um...

180
00:13:05,818 --> 00:13:06,952
Why do you call me Arikeeno?

181
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:09,255
Do you like it?

182
00:13:14,059 --> 00:13:16,694
Deep-fried frogs, pig brain stir-fry,

183
00:13:16,695 --> 00:13:19,899
braised ox penis in curry sauce,
and duck blood.

184
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:23,068
I'm going to devour them all.

185
00:13:27,373 --> 00:13:28,807
I'll have the boiled Chinese dumplings.

186
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:31,210
‎Boiled Chinese dumplings?
‎Okay, just a second.

187
00:13:46,458 --> 00:13:48,561
These are delicious, so you know.

188
00:13:52,631 --> 00:13:54,567
By the way, Arikeeno. I got something.

189
00:13:57,336 --> 00:14:01,807
I wanted to trace Candy's activities
from yesterday.

190
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:06,377
I went to the anime shop in Yoyogi
which she visited

191
00:14:06,378 --> 00:14:08,280
and accessed
their security camera footage.

192
00:14:09,481 --> 00:14:11,383
She went in around 4:30 pm.

193
00:14:12,384 --> 00:14:13,886
Look at what happens next.

194
00:14:21,126 --> 00:14:24,362
You can tell from this
that they're talking to each other.

195
00:14:24,363 --> 00:14:26,831
That means he's either Chinese

196
00:14:26,832 --> 00:14:29,201
or can speak Chinese.

197
00:14:30,836 --> 00:14:31,803
I also found out

198
00:14:31,804 --> 00:14:34,940
that they left the shop
and took a taxi together after this.

199
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:39,478
Do you remember seeing these two?

200
00:14:42,615 --> 00:14:45,084
Oh, yes. I definitely remember them.

201
00:14:46,151 --> 00:14:47,653
I drove them to Kabuki-cho.

202
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:53,225
They were both carrying big anime bags.

203
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:59,164
That's all I know so far
about her movements.

204
00:15:00,699 --> 00:15:02,568
There are two possibilities.

205
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:04,870
The first possibility.

206
00:15:06,472 --> 00:15:10,743
Candy met the man of her destiny
in a foreign land

207
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:16,115
and they're still together somewhere,
making out, unwilling to part.

208
00:15:16,849 --> 00:15:18,550
That's the "Romantic Rendezvous Theory."

209
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:20,853
And the second possibility.

210
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:25,157
The man turns out to be a criminal
preying on his fellow countrymen,

211
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:29,295
and Candy got caught up in some trouble.

212
00:15:30,062 --> 00:15:31,897
The "Critical Situation Theory."

213
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:38,370
I hope this case
follows the Rendezvous Theory.

214
00:15:44,410 --> 00:15:47,646
Now I want to hear your theory.

215
00:15:52,651 --> 00:15:55,154
Candy went missing by her own choice.

216
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,290
She herself is the criminal.

217
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:00,792
What do you mean?

218
00:16:00,793 --> 00:16:04,163
She entered the country
with a fake passport to work illegally,

219
00:16:04,964 --> 00:16:07,800
all while disguising herself as a tourist.

220
00:16:09,868 --> 00:16:11,470
Isn't that a bit of a stretch?

221
00:16:12,338 --> 00:16:13,906
I'm talking about a possibility.

222
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:18,277
If Candy got caught up in trouble,

223
00:16:18,844 --> 00:16:22,581
why doesn't she ask her friend Shen
or the police for help?

224
00:16:23,082 --> 00:16:27,018
Maybe she's being held against her will
by that smooth talker,

225
00:16:27,019 --> 00:16:29,587
or maybe she's injured and can't move.

226
00:16:29,588 --> 00:16:31,757
Then, it's possible she's already dead.

227
00:16:34,626 --> 00:16:35,861
You're very pessimistic.

228
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:39,832
It's just another possibility.

229
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:44,737
Still,

230
00:16:45,904 --> 00:16:47,973
you've managed to bring me down.

231
00:16:51,276 --> 00:16:54,146
With your mouth full of ox penis,
you don't seem so down.

232
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:57,549
Of course,

233
00:16:58,117 --> 00:17:03,121
I have the worst-case scenario
in mind too. But still...

234
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:06,592
If you can't face the harsh reality,
quit the detective work.

235
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:12,197
Suspects always lie, no matter how hard
you try to show sympathy.

236
00:17:12,998 --> 00:17:14,733
Not all of them deserve sympathy.

237
00:17:16,502 --> 00:17:19,038
Besides, some of the cops
are scumbags too.

238
00:17:23,842 --> 00:17:27,146
Is that why you quit your job?
I mean, as a cop?

239
00:17:30,015 --> 00:17:32,017
Someone at the station told me.

240
00:17:32,818 --> 00:17:35,653
You were Sergeant Ryo Arikino.

241
00:17:35,654 --> 00:17:39,091
You were at the Kamiazabu Police Station
until about three years ago.

242
00:17:39,825 --> 00:17:41,627
Why did you become an interpreter?

243
00:17:44,029 --> 00:17:45,564
I heard about you, too.

244
00:17:47,666 --> 00:17:50,502
The "Crumb Handler
of the International Division".

245
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:53,104
What the heck is that? Who--

246
00:17:53,105 --> 00:17:55,807
You can't blame them for calling you that

247
00:17:55,808 --> 00:17:57,876
when you keep reacting
to small issues like today.

248
00:18:00,512 --> 00:18:01,513
You do have a point.

249
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:07,119
At the International Division,
any issue that doesn't seem significant

250
00:18:07,719 --> 00:18:09,922
tends to get pushed to the back burner.

251
00:18:12,391 --> 00:18:13,592
All right, then.

252
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:15,594
Now what?

253
00:18:16,995 --> 00:18:18,530
You ate enough, right?

254
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:21,967
Let's go find Candy.

255
00:18:33,946 --> 00:18:35,881
Excuse me. Pardon me.

256
00:18:36,648 --> 00:18:37,849
Can I ask you something?

257
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:38,984
Arikeeno, please.

258
00:18:39,985 --> 00:18:41,019
Wait.

259
00:18:42,888 --> 00:18:43,989
This way.

260
00:18:44,556 --> 00:18:45,991
I can't keep up.

261
00:18:57,035 --> 00:18:58,536
"I've never seen them.

262
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:01,305
I visit this anime shop a lot,

263
00:19:01,306 --> 00:19:03,408
but there are
just too many tourists around."

264
00:19:04,576 --> 00:19:05,944
I see.

265
00:19:06,678 --> 00:19:07,579
Thank you.

266
00:19:13,218 --> 00:19:17,389
<i>Do you know the percentage
of foreign residents in Tokyo?</i>

267
00:19:18,657 --> 00:19:20,225
<i>It's 4.8%.</i>

268
00:19:21,527 --> 00:19:24,062
That sounds small.

269
00:19:25,531 --> 00:19:28,834
But it's actually 680,000 people,

270
00:19:31,103 --> 00:19:33,739
which means,
there are as many lives out there.

271
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,481
Shen will continue her life in Tokyo.

272
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:45,851
<i>When her friend went missing,</i>

273
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:48,320
<i>no one searched for her.</i>

274
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:52,157
<i>Imagine living in Japan,</i>

275
00:19:54,493 --> 00:19:57,029
<i>thinking nobody helps in this country.</i>

276
00:19:58,397 --> 00:19:59,631
<i>That's just too sad.</i>

277
00:20:06,338 --> 00:20:08,974
And... it's just how I am.

278
00:20:10,442 --> 00:20:12,444
Even if there's a hidden agenda,

279
00:20:13,178 --> 00:20:16,615
I don't want to believe it
unless I see it with my own eyes.

280
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:27,359
If you keep working like that,
it'll break you one day.

281
00:20:34,132 --> 00:20:34,967
What?

282
00:20:35,968 --> 00:20:38,036
Have you seen too much
of the harsh reality?

283
00:20:40,005 --> 00:20:43,942
Is that why you stopped believing
in the police or society?

284
00:20:47,713 --> 00:20:49,514
You, Arikeeno,

285
00:20:50,782 --> 00:20:52,884
are an interpreter.

286
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:56,622
But you're not a translation app or AI.

287
00:20:57,856 --> 00:20:59,458
You have your own words

288
00:21:00,225 --> 00:21:01,193
and your own thoughts.

289
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:07,299
So, you should connect more
with the world around you.

290
00:21:17,042 --> 00:21:17,976
Let's go find her.

291
00:21:30,122 --> 00:21:31,657
You're too random.

292
00:21:46,505 --> 00:21:48,239
Oh, yes. These two.

293
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:49,308
You know them?

294
00:21:49,841 --> 00:21:51,243
They were here yesterday.

295
00:21:53,512 --> 00:21:54,545
This is amazing.

296
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:56,581
Your hunch was absolutely spot on.

297
00:21:58,150 --> 00:22:01,586
Can you describe how she was?

298
00:22:03,689 --> 00:22:07,091
She was really drunk.
They left around 2:00 am,

299
00:22:07,092 --> 00:22:10,429
but she could barely stand,
with him helping her.

300
00:22:12,497 --> 00:22:15,500
Congratulations.
It seems like a rendezvous.

301
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:20,305
One more thing.

302
00:22:21,506 --> 00:22:24,176
Do you know anything about this man?

303
00:22:26,011 --> 00:22:28,380
I often see him here.

304
00:22:29,815 --> 00:22:31,549
I think he was called Henry.

305
00:22:31,550 --> 00:22:32,517
Is he a regular?

306
00:22:33,919 --> 00:22:35,854
Where is he from? What does he do?

307
00:22:39,057 --> 00:22:43,228
Why did you bring her here?

308
00:22:43,862 --> 00:22:46,798
It's very unusual for you to help someone.

309
00:22:47,799 --> 00:22:50,168
She was not very efficient.

310
00:22:50,936 --> 00:22:53,572
So, you brought her to me,
the one "in the know"?

311
00:22:54,072 --> 00:22:59,811
I'm surprised
you'd do something for your colleague.

312
00:23:03,448 --> 00:23:06,551
Or maybe you are his girlfriend?

313
00:23:09,821 --> 00:23:11,123
Absolutely not.

314
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:14,292
I could tell.

315
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:18,530
But I don't really feel like cooperating.

316
00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:31,943
I don't have the authority
to investigate or make arrests.

317
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:36,548
On the other hand,
she's an active detective.

318
00:23:37,149 --> 00:23:40,652
If you don't want her to suspect,
just answer her questions.

319
00:23:46,024 --> 00:23:48,059
Go down to the underpass at the snake sign

320
00:23:49,161 --> 00:23:51,396
after you pass
one of the Chinese restaurants.

321
00:23:52,998 --> 00:23:54,099
Snake sign?

322
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:05,143
It's here.

323
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:12,884
You don't have it yet?
Are you messing with me?

324
00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:19,458
Go find it quickly or I'm gonna kill you.

325
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:23,061
Excuse me.

326
00:24:24,496 --> 00:24:26,765
Can I talk to you for a moment?

327
00:24:27,566 --> 00:24:29,668
I'll be real quick.

328
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:33,838
Wait, wait, wait.

329
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:36,708
Hey, wait. Stop right there.

330
00:24:40,645 --> 00:24:41,713
Stop.

331
00:24:42,614 --> 00:24:43,815
It's all right.

332
00:25:14,913 --> 00:25:17,482
Give me a moment. I'm so sorry.

333
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:19,451
Henry...

334
00:25:22,754 --> 00:25:25,190
this man in this picture is you, right?

335
00:25:26,124 --> 00:25:28,492
I know no Japanese.

336
00:25:28,493 --> 00:25:30,495
You don't have to know Japanese.

337
00:25:31,062 --> 00:25:31,963
He's interpreting.

338
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:36,968
"Is this man in the picture you?"

339
00:25:48,680 --> 00:25:51,682
"I hit it off with her
and had drinks with her in a club.

340
00:25:51,683 --> 00:25:54,085
But we parted after 2:00 am."

341
00:25:55,620 --> 00:25:57,389
Where did you part with her?

342
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,128
"Near the club."

343
00:26:05,497 --> 00:26:09,734
Then, why did you run
when I talked to you?

344
00:26:18,610 --> 00:26:21,880
"Because my Residence Card
is at my apartment."

345
00:26:24,883 --> 00:26:25,984
Is that right?

346
00:26:26,618 --> 00:26:27,752
I guess I scared you.

347
00:26:29,287 --> 00:26:30,221
I'm sorry.

348
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,193
You really believe
what this guy is saying?

349
00:26:36,061 --> 00:26:37,362
Why do you say that?

350
00:26:43,702 --> 00:26:46,972
You bought that bag
at that anime shop, right?

351
00:26:49,140 --> 00:26:50,208
Let me take a look?

352
00:26:50,976 --> 00:26:51,875
Just for a moment.

353
00:26:51,876 --> 00:26:53,444
‎What right do you have to do this?

354
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:56,348
You don't have to be embarrassed about it.

355
00:26:57,582 --> 00:26:58,850
This is so cute.

356
00:26:59,718 --> 00:27:01,720
‎What right do you have to take my things?

357
00:27:02,854 --> 00:27:04,055
‎Move aside.

358
00:27:07,025 --> 00:27:08,226
‎Get out of the way.

359
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:13,231
Tell me where Candy is.

360
00:27:14,132 --> 00:27:15,165
What did you do to her?

361
00:27:15,166 --> 00:27:16,201
Miss Koda...

362
00:27:19,871 --> 00:27:21,939
You said you parted with her.

363
00:27:21,940 --> 00:27:22,940
PASSPORT

364
00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:25,744
If you parted with her near the club,
why do you have that?

365
00:27:26,878 --> 00:27:28,046
I haven't done anything.

366
00:27:28,413 --> 00:27:29,714
Tell me where Candy is.

367
00:27:31,249 --> 00:27:34,319
I need to see your ID.
Take out your wallet.

368
00:27:49,768 --> 00:27:50,602
‎My wallet.

369
00:27:52,003 --> 00:27:52,837
‎For what?

370
00:27:55,774 --> 00:27:56,741
‎Move aside.

371
00:27:57,575 --> 00:27:58,610
This is marijuana.

372
00:28:05,183 --> 00:28:07,018
Was Candy really drunk

373
00:28:07,986 --> 00:28:09,688
only because of alcohol?

374
00:28:12,023 --> 00:28:14,993
You took her stuff using this, didn't you?

375
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:36,980
I think our stuff
got mixed up at the club.

376
00:28:36,981 --> 00:28:40,552
I'll be in big trouble
if I don't get my bag back soon.

377
00:28:41,786 --> 00:28:45,623
Bag?

378
00:28:46,858 --> 00:28:49,461
That bag is not mine.

379
00:28:53,131 --> 00:28:55,033
- What's the matter?
- It's nothing.

380
00:28:57,368 --> 00:28:58,870
You don't look like it's nothing.

381
00:29:01,106 --> 00:29:03,841
I have no say in the investigation
and I'm not certain.

382
00:29:03,842 --> 00:29:07,378
That's not right.
Don't hold back all of a sudden.

383
00:29:12,650 --> 00:29:15,986
A woman was arrested this morning
for skipping out on a taxi fare,

384
00:29:15,987 --> 00:29:19,490
and a large amount of drugs
was found in her possession.

385
00:29:19,491 --> 00:29:21,725
Is she being questioned by our division?

386
00:29:21,726 --> 00:29:22,627
Yes.

387
00:29:23,962 --> 00:29:26,631
I'm not really certain
this is related, though.

388
00:29:27,532 --> 00:29:28,565
But still...

389
00:29:28,566 --> 00:29:30,268
Is it a former cop's hunch?

390
00:29:32,303 --> 00:29:33,838
It's an interpreter's hunch.

391
00:29:35,940 --> 00:29:37,642
Thank you for your patience.

392
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:44,882
This is the list.

393
00:29:44,883 --> 00:29:45,884
Thank you.

394
00:29:47,385 --> 00:29:49,187
"November 6th."

395
00:29:50,288 --> 00:29:52,757
November 6th...

396
00:29:58,730 --> 00:29:59,864
I found it. It's here.

397
00:30:11,509 --> 00:30:12,377
Arikeeno, what's this?

398
00:30:22,487 --> 00:30:24,155
"Give me back my bag."

399
00:30:24,823 --> 00:30:26,825
"I'll return your passport in exchange."

400
00:30:27,458 --> 00:30:30,261
"Don't keep ignoring me. Where are you?"

401
00:30:31,062 --> 00:30:32,497
"I'm gonna kill you."

402
00:30:40,138 --> 00:30:41,606
This bag is...

403
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:01,926
Your name

404
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:06,297
is He Zihao, isn't it?

405
00:31:09,500 --> 00:31:12,803
The day before yesterday,
you visited an anime shop in Yoyogi,

406
00:31:12,804 --> 00:31:15,506
where a Chinese man living
in Tokyo approached you.

407
00:31:24,616 --> 00:31:25,884
Are you from China?

408
00:31:28,319 --> 00:31:33,257
My nephew asked me
to buy some Japan-exclusive goods,

409
00:31:33,258 --> 00:31:34,592
but I'm not sure which ones they are.

410
00:31:35,693 --> 00:31:37,528
This is exclusive to Japan.

411
00:31:38,563 --> 00:31:40,998
It's cute. Thanks.

412
00:31:40,999 --> 00:31:43,101
Is this your first time in Japan?

413
00:31:43,768 --> 00:31:45,603
I can show you around town.

414
00:31:49,340 --> 00:31:50,575
Sorry, it was kind of abrupt.

415
00:31:51,142 --> 00:31:53,978
I'm Henry.
I'm a university student in Japan.

416
00:31:54,979 --> 00:31:57,749
- My name is Candy.
- Candy? Nice to meet you.

417
00:32:00,184 --> 00:32:02,220
Tokyo is so bright at night, isn't it?

418
00:32:03,688 --> 00:32:05,657
Why don't you lower the window?

419
00:32:35,720 --> 00:32:36,554
‎What are you doing? Let's go.

420
00:32:52,303 --> 00:32:53,771
Do you have anything in your pockets?

421
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:56,975
Put them all in the bag.

422
00:33:02,747 --> 00:33:04,349
Let's go.

423
00:33:11,356 --> 00:33:12,490
Are you nervous?

424
00:33:14,292 --> 00:33:16,194
You have to have fun.

425
00:33:16,694 --> 00:33:17,662
‎Okay.

426
00:33:56,601 --> 00:33:57,802
Do you want to smoke this?

427
00:34:05,410 --> 00:34:06,911
Press here as you smoke.

428
00:34:16,187 --> 00:34:18,322
Take another drag.

429
00:35:07,705 --> 00:35:10,975
Are you okay?
Shall we go somewhere you can rest?

430
00:35:11,742 --> 00:35:12,977
I want to drink some water.

431
00:35:13,177 --> 00:35:16,013
If we go to a hotel,
you can drink water and relax.

432
00:35:18,316 --> 00:35:21,551
Please go buy some water for me.

433
00:35:21,552 --> 00:35:23,521
Wait here.

434
00:35:24,222 --> 00:35:25,923
Don't go anywhere.

435
00:35:28,192 --> 00:35:32,195
<i>Feeling completely drunk,
you realized you were in danger.</i>

436
00:35:32,196 --> 00:35:34,432
<i>And you managed to get away from there.</i>

437
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:39,537
But after that, more trouble awaited you.

438
00:35:45,176 --> 00:35:48,613
You mixed up your bag with his

439
00:35:49,213 --> 00:35:51,449
and ended up taking his
instead of your own.

440
00:36:02,293 --> 00:36:05,829
<i>Where are you? Give me back my bag.</i>

441
00:36:05,830 --> 00:36:07,265
<i>Don't you dare tell anyone what's inside.</i>

442
00:36:23,814 --> 00:36:24,649
Are you all right?

443
00:36:25,583 --> 00:36:27,684
<i>In the bag you took,</i>

444
00:36:27,685 --> 00:36:30,588
<i>there was a large amount
of liquid marijuana.</i>

445
00:36:48,105 --> 00:36:51,709
DAD

446
00:36:54,245 --> 00:36:56,079
ARE YOU HAVING A GOOD TIME?

447
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:58,983
SEND ME MANY PICTURES.
DON'T STAY OUT TOO LATE.

448
00:37:09,026 --> 00:37:10,494
‎Dad.

449
00:37:13,364 --> 00:37:14,532
‎Dad.

450
00:37:17,868 --> 00:37:18,903
‎Dad.

451
00:37:22,740 --> 00:37:23,708
‎Dad.

452
00:37:28,546 --> 00:37:29,647
At that time,

453
00:37:30,314 --> 00:37:32,316
you didn't have a wallet
in your possession.

454
00:37:32,817 --> 00:37:35,385
You were accused of skipping a taxi fare,

455
00:37:35,386 --> 00:37:38,656
and liquid marijuana
was found in your possession.

456
00:37:40,358 --> 00:37:41,325
Moreover,

457
00:37:42,159 --> 00:37:45,363
your urine test came back positive
for drugs.

458
00:37:48,366 --> 00:37:49,900
If you reveal your real name,

459
00:37:50,534 --> 00:37:53,570
the police may contact your embassy.

460
00:37:53,571 --> 00:37:56,507
And your family will find out
that you got arrested.

461
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:01,379
In China,

462
00:38:02,079 --> 00:38:05,182
drug violation is a felony,
punishable by death penalty.

463
00:38:08,853 --> 00:38:09,820
Knowing that,

464
00:38:11,722 --> 00:38:12,923
you were terrified, right?

465
00:38:16,694 --> 00:38:19,964
That's why you remained silent.

466
00:38:21,766 --> 00:38:24,302
Isn't that right, Candy?

467
00:38:31,542 --> 00:38:32,677
We were...

468
00:38:38,649 --> 00:38:41,085
We've been searching for you
this whole time.

469
00:38:47,425 --> 00:38:50,094
Please interpret exactly as I said.

470
00:38:54,632 --> 00:38:56,033
"I was...

471
00:38:57,201 --> 00:39:01,772
We've been searching
for you this whole time."

472
00:39:04,809 --> 00:39:08,212
Being detained for 40 hours
without understanding the language,

473
00:39:10,581 --> 00:39:12,883
you must have been very scared.

474
00:39:16,987 --> 00:39:17,888
But don't worry.

475
00:39:19,623 --> 00:39:20,791
You're all right now.

476
00:39:59,430 --> 00:40:01,132
Candy! Candy!

477
00:40:23,821 --> 00:40:25,623
Thank you so much.

478
00:40:27,057 --> 00:40:28,292
You're welcome.

479
00:40:32,663 --> 00:40:35,633
You can go back to your family now.

480
00:40:37,368 --> 00:40:38,402
Thank you.

481
00:40:39,270 --> 00:40:40,604
Thank you so much.

482
00:40:44,642 --> 00:40:45,576
Here it is.

483
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:49,413
Candy.

484
00:41:07,665 --> 00:41:10,767
TOKYO METROPOLITAN POLICE
INTERPRETATION CENTER

485
00:41:10,768 --> 00:41:13,770
Mr. Arikino, did you just get back?

486
00:41:13,771 --> 00:41:14,804
Yes, I did.

487
00:41:14,805 --> 00:41:19,142
I'm going to have lunch
at a new Vietnamese restaurant nearby.

488
00:41:19,143 --> 00:41:20,811
Would you like to join me?

489
00:41:22,847 --> 00:41:24,415
I'll be out all afternoon, so...

490
00:41:25,216 --> 00:41:26,283
I see.

491
00:41:27,084 --> 00:41:28,919
I'll invite you another time then.

492
00:41:33,591 --> 00:41:34,825
You invite him often.

493
00:41:35,793 --> 00:41:37,961
If you have a crush on him, give up.

494
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:39,830
This was the fifth time.

495
00:41:40,731 --> 00:41:42,900
Kurosu, that's a form
of sexual harassment.

496
00:41:43,901 --> 00:41:45,970
Just think about it. It's Mr. Arikino.

497
00:41:46,537 --> 00:41:48,771
He distances himself from everybody.

498
00:41:48,772 --> 00:41:51,441
I'm totally convinced that he despises me.

499
00:41:51,442 --> 00:41:53,743
I'm pretty sure that's not the case.

500
00:41:53,744 --> 00:41:57,047
But I admit
that he sure is very difficult to read.

501
00:41:59,617 --> 00:42:00,884
Here's your salad bowl.

502
00:42:00,885 --> 00:42:03,987
- Thanks.
- Sure.

503
00:42:03,988 --> 00:42:06,390
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

504
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:09,026
You know what, Arikeeno?

505
00:42:10,127 --> 00:42:11,327
Don't you think...

506
00:42:11,328 --> 00:42:12,228
ORIGINAL STORY BY KUROMARU

507
00:42:12,229 --> 00:42:14,331
...we'll make pretty good partners?

508
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:18,769
Tokyo is a city

509
00:42:20,671 --> 00:42:22,039
like a salad bowl of ethnicities.

510
00:42:23,841 --> 00:42:27,077
It's not a melting pot
where races merge with each other.

511
00:42:27,912 --> 00:42:31,414
Here, people from various
backgrounds coexist.

512
00:42:31,415 --> 00:42:32,616
So, it's a salad bowl.

513
00:42:36,453 --> 00:42:38,055
Though there are so many foreigners,

514
00:42:38,622 --> 00:42:41,224
very few detectives are experienced
in dealing with them.

515
00:42:41,225 --> 00:42:43,494
And even fewer speak foreign languages.

516
00:42:44,962 --> 00:42:47,730
I'm ashamed to admit

517
00:42:47,731 --> 00:42:52,069
that I can barely carry on
everyday conversations in English.

518
00:42:52,736 --> 00:42:53,704
All that to say,

519
00:42:54,271 --> 00:42:58,676
let's pick all the crumbs
of the International Division together.

520
00:43:02,379 --> 00:43:03,447
Is that a pick-up line?

521
00:43:04,048 --> 00:43:05,481
Sure, it is.

522
00:43:05,482 --> 00:43:07,284
We're a team of crumb-gathering heroes.

523
00:43:11,055 --> 00:43:14,758
If you need me, you can request me
through the Interpretation Center.

524
00:43:20,598 --> 00:43:21,764
There.

525
00:43:21,765 --> 00:43:23,667
You should eat more vegetables.

526
00:43:24,268 --> 00:43:25,269
Give it back.

527
00:43:26,704 --> 00:43:28,872
- I'll take one.
- Look. There's an alligator.

528
00:43:31,942 --> 00:43:34,110
"Heaven's vengeance is slow but sure!"

529
00:43:34,111 --> 00:43:36,179
Thank you. You are wonderful.

530
00:43:36,180 --> 00:43:38,481
Do you even have a clue about him?

531
00:43:38,482 --> 00:43:41,050
Well, he's definitely odd.

532
00:43:41,051 --> 00:43:42,785
You had three batteries in your backpack.

533
00:43:42,786 --> 00:43:44,687
Why did you go there alone?

534
00:43:44,688 --> 00:43:46,924
Arikeeno was the one
who leaked information?

535
00:43:49,159 --> 00:43:50,694
What's going on? Koda?

536
00:43:56,166 --> 00:43:58,068
<i>Henry was busted.</i>

537
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:00,704
I see.

538
00:44:02,139 --> 00:44:03,273
Are we safe?

539
00:44:03,907 --> 00:44:05,208
<i>So far, yes.</i>

540
00:44:05,209 --> 00:44:08,779
<i>But they have all the bags.</i>

541
00:44:14,752 --> 00:44:16,519
Make sure you take care of it.

542
00:44:16,520 --> 00:44:18,188
Clean up all the connections.

543
00:44:18,389 --> 00:44:20,190
<i>All right.</i>
